uname, /bin/uname.sh
alias: 'uname'

Print system identification: ReMinux
version, kernel host string, the
computer label and id, and Lua
runtime.

Usage:
  uname [-a|-s|-r|-n|-m]

  -a  all (default)
  -s  kernel/system name
  -r  ReMinux release/version
  -n  computer label
  -m  Lua/architecture
